Definition: You will be given two pieces of text with the same meaning. One of them is simpler and easier to understand for non-native English speakers.  Text two: From the start, it was chosen to be a duty-free port to compete with the neighboring Sultanate of Pattani for trade.

Positive Examples.input:

Positive Examples.explanation: Text one is shorter and it doesn't contain unnecessary phrases.

Positive Examples.input:

Positive Examples.explanation: The second text contains shorter sentences which are easier to understand.

Negative Examples.input:
